  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining the Application**\n\nI\'ve clarified the project scope. The user isn\'t just seeking a generic Android app; they want a \"SoulJournal\" or \"Ethereal Journal\" application with specific screen designs presented in the HTML. I\'m now focused on understanding the layouts and functionality implied by those visuals, particularly the \"Today / AI\" screen, and how it informs the app\'s overall structure.\n\n\n**Analyzing the \"Today\" Screen**\n\nI\'m now diving deep into the \"Today / AI Summary\" modal\'s design. The overlay, elevated bottom sheet, and the specific sections (Milestones, Actionable Vectors, Emotional Tone) are becoming clearer. The functional diary dashboard behind the modal is a core element. I\'m considering how this modal interaction informs the user journey, and the role of the \"Refine,\" \"Copy,\" and \"Share\" buttons within that flow. I\'m also planning out the onboarding.\n\n\n**Designing the Initial Interface**\n\nI\'m now sketching out the app\'s initial screen: a sophisticated opening interface. It has a calming background gradient with a subtle paper texture. The circular logo, an open book icon set in deep indigo, sits at the center, accompanied by the \"SoulJournal\" title in elegant serif font. Rotating phrases like \"Write your mind,\" and \"Speak your day\" provide intrigue. A warm morning light journal and pen mockup image evokes a sense of ease. I\'m noting the \"Sign in with Google\" button with the Google logo, along with the privacy subtext. There\'s a version string at the bottom too.\n\n\n**Evaluating Firebase Integration**\n\nI\'m now determining if implementing Firebase is suitable. The \"Sign in with Google\" element suggests the need for user accounts. I think Firebase Auth and Firestore would provide robust and durable persistence for journal entries and the AI summary generation. I\'ve performed a skill check, and the skills confirm that Firebase\'s persistence capabilities are relevant. Now I\'m considering integrating this with the Google Sign In, and also the Gemini API.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will examine the `package.json` file to understand the current configuration and dependencies."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 6
      nanos: 86996614
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
