  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing the User Experience**\n\nI\'m now diving into the user experience design for the React application. My focus is on ensuring the application seamlessly fits within a beautifully designed Android mockup frame on desktop. This means thinking about how to create a high-fidelity mobile app experience running in a desktop browser.\n\n\n**Refining the Onboarding Screen**\n\nI\'m currently focusing on the onboarding screen design. The goal is a striking visual experience. I\'m prioritizing the open book icon within a `bg-journal-primary` circle. Text color will be white. I\'m implementing \"SoulJournal\" in EB Garamond display. A React hook and `setInterval` will animate a cycling tagline to match the mock: \"Write your mind,\" \"Speak your day,\" and \"Scan your journal.\" I\'m using the tabletop image at the provided URL.\n\n\n**Implementing Google Login**\n\nI\'m now integrating the \"Sign in with Google\" button. On click, I\'ll simulate a Google account selector overlay, complete with a beautiful, animated headshot and account selection (e.g., \"Chinmay\" - chinmayrk01@gmail.com). Upon selection, I plan to handle the login and gracefully transition to the dashboard, with a nice animation. My next focus is the Dashboard screen.\n\n\n**Designing the Dashboard**\n\nI\'m now turning my attention to the dashboard layout. I envision a circular avatar on the left, which will expand to a profile panel on click, or sign-out. The \"Today\" title will be in Garamond, and settings will be accessible via a gear icon on the right, displaying mock data reset, theme toggle, and account details. A scrollable container will house journal entries, starting with a mock \"Morning Reflection\" with mood and content. I also aim to include functionality for adding new entries, with rich text input, mood tags, and a Voice Mode with waveform visualization.\n\n\n**Adding the AI Summary Feature**\n\nI\'m now integrating an AI summary feature to the dashboard. I\'ve decided on a floating action button (FAB), or dynamic bar, labeled \"AI Summary\". It\'ll trigger a slide-up \"AI Summary\" Bottom Sheet. Clicking this will call a server-side API endpoint, `/api/summarize`, using today\'s entries. The Bottom Sheet will have a scrim background, elevated container, a handle, and a close button. It\'ll display a title, an atmospheric visual with a gradient and a \"DEEP INSIGHT\" pill, and the AI-generated summary.\n\n\n**Enhancing the AI Summary**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the visual and functional aspects of the AI Summary Bottom Sheet. I\'m building on the existing framework: atmospheric visual area (like a calming color mesh) and ensuring that the content sections mirror the mockup\'s style. I\'ll implement \"Milestones,\" \"Actionable Vectors,\" and \"Emotional Tone\" sections, each with distinct bullet icons and EB Garamond headlines. I\'m also adding a footer with interactive feedback chips: \"Refine Summary\" to trigger Gemini prompts for refinement, a \"Copy to Clipboard\" button with a success toast, and a \"Share Log\" button to activate the Android share sheet. Finally, I\'m framing the entire screen inside a high-end Android mobile app mockup shell, complete with a top status bar (time, wifi, battery, signal icons).\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/components/PhoneFrame.tsx`, which wraps the Ethereal Journal application in a polished Android device mockup with a functional status bar (syncing with the user\'s real local time, battery, and signal), while remaining fully responsive so it adapts to true mobile screens seamlessly."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 10
      nanos: 544631157
    }
