    thinking: "**Updating Color Palettes**\n\nI\'m now changing the background color in `src/index.css` to the warm ivory/cream shade, matching the provided design specs. The previous soft lavender is being replaced to align with the **Vibrant Palette** theme. This is the first step of this task.\n\n\n**Defining Color Values**\n\nI\'ve defined the new color variables based on the vibrant palette. Primary text and accents will use `#1E293B`, and `#F43F5E` is now the primary highlight color. Teal is updated to `#6366F1`, and the background is a clean ivory/cream at `#FDFCFB`. I\'m using `#F1F5F9` for low-emphasis cards, and `#E2E8F0` for borders. Also I will be setting a gradient for the featured summary header as `linear-gradient(135deg, #6366F1, #A855F7, #F43F5E)`.\n\n\n"
