digo for milestones. I\'m also changing list-disc bullets to matching badge colors. In the footer, I\'m updating the button styles to have a very high-end aesthetic, with subtle, elegant colors and border styles. I\'m aiming for a cohesive feel by improving the \"Refine Summary,\" \"Copy to Clipboard,\" and \"Share Log\" buttons. This will be implemented in `/src/components/AISummarySheet.tsx`.\n\n\n**Verifying File Elements**\n\nI\'m now diving into the file contents to make exact, pinpoint adjustments, verifying all elements are aligned. I\'m focusing on lines 63 and onward, or in chunks using `multi_edit_file`. I\'m starting by carefully reviewing and refining the header styling, specifically lines 73-85 of `/src/components/AISummarySheet.tsx`, to integrate the design elements precisely.\n\n\n**Updating Loading State**\n\nI\'m now incorporating changes to the loading state to improve its appearance. I\'m focusing on the animation and visual elements within lines 89-111 of `/src/components/AISummarySheet.tsx`, aiming to create a more dynamic and engaging loading experience for the user. I\'m working to make the visual cues more clear and modern, and to make it feel better overall.\n\n\n**Refining Visual Cues**\n\nI\'m now implementing the loading state design. I am focusing on the visual cues, as indicated by the code. Specifically, I\'m integrating a spinning animation and a pulsating auto_awesome icon to provide feedback. The informational text is also being updated for clarity and engagement, alongside error state.\n\n\n\n**Refining Error State**\n\nI\'m now integrating an error state fallback within `/src/components/AISummarySheet.tsx`. I\'ve added a visual indicator to inform the user when the summary is unavailable. This is included in the new design in order to improve usability. I\'m focusing on lines 114 to 127 to ensure that the user gets an informative message.\n\n\n**Integrating Loaded State**\n\nI\'m now focusing on implementing the fully-loaded state