egantly designing the \"Stats\" tab\'s dashboard interface, including a title and a subheading. I\'ve considered creating a ring chart, and will create a gauge representing energy using either a custom SVG or CSS-rendered circular design.\n\n\n**Designing Interactive Data**\n\nI\'m now focusing on interactive data visualization within the \"Stats\" tab. I plan to incorporate a dynamic ring chart showing an \"Energy\" value, possibly computed from user entries. The user should be able to toggle/regenerate metrics, enhancing interactivity. I\'m also styling data pills for metrics like steps, sleep, and logged entries. I\'m also considering creating a dominant mood card to show how each day is going. I\'m also refining the \"AI Summary\" tab to inline the existing summary with a call to action if no daily summary is currently available.\n\n\n**Implementing AI Tab**\n\nI\'m now fully focused on the \"AI Summary\" tab\'s interactive components. I\'m refining the tab layout to showcase milestones, actionable vectors, emotional tone, and the refinement chat. This chat input, placed at the bottom, allows direct interaction with the AI via text prompts. Users can also copy and share summaries easily. I\'m removing the old `AISummarySheet` because everything is now beautifully integrated! I\'m planning state management by refactoring `App.tsx` to handle fetching the summary data!\n\n\n"
