    thinking: "**Developing Navigation System**\n\nI\'ve successfully created the basic types in `types.ts`. I\'m now transitioning my focus to a robust bottom tab navigation system to replace `DashboardScreen.tsx`. This will encompass a Journal tab with a calendar, new entry editor (with voice input), and a reflection list, plus a Stats tab. I\'m making good progress on this navigation framework.\n\n\n**Designing Dynamic Dashboards**\n\nI\'m now integrating dynamic, calculated metrics into the dashboard, inspired by the Vibrant Palette\'s Device 2 design, and I\'m quite excited! I\'m creating an energy radial ring chart, featuring animations and SVG styling. Also, I\'m working on a steps counter, sleep counter, and a logged words counter that dynamically sums entries. I\'ve also planned a visual mood balance graph.\n\n\n**Refining Screen Layout**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the visual layout of `DashboardScreen.tsx`. My current task is to implement a sticky bottom tab bar, incorporating the design elements from the mockup. I\'m building it as an absolute-positioned element to stay fixed at the bottom, while the main content scrolls. I\'m using `flex` properties to manage content arrangement and `overflow` to manage scrolling. I\'m focusing on ensuring responsiveness for various screen sizes.\n\n\n**Implementing Interactive Dashboard**\n\nI\'m now writing the `DashboardScreen.tsx` code and making it highly interactive. I\'m focusing on the steps and sleep widgets, along with an energy radial ring chart that dynamically updates based on user interaction. There\'s a share option that triggers a share popup, and also a refinement input that triggers an AI summary, providing a great UX. I\'m leveraging `y-auto pb-24` and absolutely/sticky positioning for the tab bar.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 61
      nanos: 25321993
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
